Package commands

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    ICommand
    An interface for classes representing database commands.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    BackupCommand
    This writes the database to a specified file.
    DefineIndexCommand
    This establishes an index, allowing specified data to be accessed more quickly.
    DefineTableCommand
    This creates a new table in the database with the specified fields.
    DeleteCommand
    This deletes fields from a table meeting a specified condition, or all fields if no condition is specified.
    DropCommand
    This deletes a specified table from the database.
    ExitCommand
    This ends the interpreter program.
    InsertCommand
    This inserts values into a table.
    IntersectCommand
    This outputs a table containing the intersection of two tables.
    JoinCommand
    This outputs a table containing the fields and elements of two tables.
    MinusCommand
    This outputs a table containing the elements of one table which are not in another table.
    OrderCommand
    This outputs the contents of a table ordered by the values in a specified field, optionally in reverse order.
    PrintCommand
    This prints the contents of a table or lists the tables in the database and their fields.
    ProjectCommand
    This outputs a table containing the elements of specified fields from a table.
    ReadCommand
    This reads and applies information about a database from a file.
    RenameCommand
    This changes the name of a table.
    RestoreCommand
    This reads database information from a file.
    SelectCommand
    This outputs the contents of a specified table, optionally with only rows meeting a specified condition included.
    UnionCommand
    This outputs the union of two specified tables.
    UpdateCommand
    This sets a field to a specified value for all rows in a table, optionally including only those rows meeting a specified condition.
